# LLM Safety & External API Resilience

## Markdown Fence Stripping (mandatory)

ALWAYS strip markdown code fences before `JSON.parse` on any LLM or Retell response:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { safeJsonParse } from "@/lib/safe-json-parse";
const data = safeJsonParse<CallSummary>(rawResponse);

// ❌ BAD — Retell/LLMs often wrap JSON in ```json ... ```
const data = JSON.parse(rawResponse);
```

Use a shared `safeJsonParse` utility (copied from SmartDesk Dental). Never parse LLM output inline without fence stripping.

## External API Calls

Wrap all calls to Retell, SignalWire, Google Calendar, Stripe, and other third-party APIs in try/catch with **typed errors**:

```typescript
class RetellApiError extends Error {
  constructor(message: string, public readonly statusCode?: number, public readonly cause?: unknown) {
    super(message);
    this.name = "RetellApiError";
  }
}
```

## Retry Logic

- Transient failures (5xx, network timeout, rate limit 429): retry with exponential backoff (max 3 attempts).
- Client errors (4xx except 429): do not retry; surface typed error to caller.
- Log each retry with context (businessId, callId, endpoint) — never log secrets.

## Post-Call Webhooks

Retell post-call payloads may include nested JSON strings. Parse defensively: strip fences, validate with Zod, default missing fields rather than crashing the webhook handler.
